Required: August 2014Curriculum: International Primary CurriculumLocation: Dubai, UAESalary: 102,000 - 168,000 Dhs £17,520 - £28,800Experience: 2 Years minimum PYPSponsorship: Single or Married Teaching CouplesContract: Two Year RenewableSchool Vision: To offer a broad international education, designed for local and expatriate students, promoting excellence in all academic activities while enhancing the educational, social and physical development of students by encouraging analytical and creative thinking in preparation for the next stage of their education.This modern school caters for 1500 students and provides an ideal setting in which children can learn, grow and develop into responsible and responsive self-starters and the whole team are committed to the student's academic, social and personal development. Operating the IPC curriculum the school nurtures the holistic development of students alongside academic success.This is a fantastic opportunity to join a forward thinking team which provides extensive development and training while working alongside professional international educators.Applicant requirements: Bachelor's degree in Education or a Primary Teaching Subject along with a relevant Teaching Certificate and 2 years solid teaching experience. Knowledge or practice of the IPC curriculum is desirable along with being flexible, adaptable and passionate about teaching.Benefits:Tax free salarySingle furnished accommodationAnnual flightsMedical insurance plus other benefits.If you wish to apply please contact your local Teachanywhere consultant who will be happy to furnish you with more information.
